This is the RAMSES parameter file for the 2D passive scalar mixing test.
A diamond shape is placed in a lower density medium which is moving to the left.
The passive scalar is set to be 1 in the diamond shape and -1 in the background medium.
Turbulence is generated in the wake at the corners of the diamond,
causing the passive scalar to mix.

&RUN_PARAMS
hydro=.true.
nremap=10
nsubcycle=10*1
/

&AMR_PARAMS
levelmin=4
levelmax=9
ngridmax=50000
nexpand=10*2
boxlen=1.0
/

&INIT_PARAMS
nregion=2
region_type(1)='square'
region_type(2)='square'
exp_region=10.0,1.0
x_center=0.5,0.6
y_center=0.5,0.5
length_x=1.0,0.5
length_y=1.0,0.5
d_region=0.1,1.0
u_region=-2.0,0.0
p_region=1.0,1.0
var_region=-1.0,1.0
/

&OUTPUT_PARAMS
noutput=1
tout=0.2
/

&HYDRO_PARAMS
gamma=1.4
courant_factor=0.8
slope_type=2
riemann='hllc'
pressure_fix=.true.
/

&REFINE_PARAMS
err_grad_d=0.05
err_grad_u=0.05
err_grad_p=0.05
interpol_var=0
interpol_type=2
/
